Tips and Tricks to do useful things! :)


Replaces all instances of first string with second string with given input file.

Command: sed -i 's/old-text/new-text/g' input.txt

      Example: sed 's/\./\-/g' map2.txt > map3.txt 
              the "\" are used to escape the "." and the "-", new output is stored in new file map3.txt
              
Display only the first column of input using AWK
  awk '{print $1}'

Search and replace using sed
  sed 's/old-text/new-text/g'

Count number of characters in a text input including null terminator
  wc -c
